@startuml Seq06_AiSpendingInsights
!theme plain
participant User
participant "React Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Insights API" as Backend
participant "Analytics\nEngine" as Analytics
participant "LLM API\n(Gemini/Groq)" as LLM
participant "MySQL DB" as DB

autonumber

Note over User,DB: **REQUEST AI INSIGHTS**

User -> Frontend: Navigate to AI Insights
Frontend -> Frontend: Show loading state
Frontend -> Backend: GET /insights/analyze?period=month

Backend -> DB: Fetch user's transaction data
Backend -> DB: SELECT * FROM transactions\nWHERE user_id AND date >= DATE_SUB(NOW(), INTERVAL 30 DAY)
DB --> Backend: [transactions]

Backend -> DB: SELECT * FROM budgets WHERE user_id
DB --> Backend: [budgets]

Backend --> Frontend: {status: "analyzing"}
Frontend -> Frontend: Show analyzing spinner

Note over User,DB: **CALCULATE ANALYTICS METRICS**

Backend -> Analytics: analyze_spending_patterns([transactions])

Analytics -> Analytics: Calculate metrics
Note over Analytics: - Total spending
Note over Analytics: - Average daily
Note over Analytics: - Top categories
Note over Analytics: - Budget variance
Note over Analytics: - Trends

Analytics -> Analytics: total_spent = 5420
Analytics -> Analytics: daily_avg = 180.67
Analytics -> Analytics: top_3 = [Food: 2100, Bills: 1340, Transport: 980]
Analytics -> Analytics: budget_vs_actual = [Food: 105%, Bills: 85%]
Analytics -> Analytics: month_prev_trend = +8.3% increase

Analytics --> Backend: {metrics: {...}}

Note over User,DB: **MONTH-ON-MONTH COMPARISON**

Backend -> Analytics: compare_months(current=May, previous=April)

Analytics -> DB: SELECT SUM(amount) by category\nFROM transactions\nWHERE user_id AND date IN May
DB --> Analytics: {may_data}

Analytics -> DB: SELECT SUM(amount) by category\nFROM transactions\nWHERE user_id AND date IN April
DB --> Analytics: {april_data}

Analytics -> Analytics: Calculate percentage changes
Analytics -> Analytics: Food: Apr 1950 → May 2100 (+7.7%)
Analytics -> Analytics: Bills: Apr 1280 → May 1340 (+4.7%)
Analytics -> Analytics: Transport: Apr 890 → May 980 (+10.1%)

Analytics --> Backend: {comparison: {...}}

Note over User,DB: **ANOMALY DETECTION**

Backend -> Analytics: detect_anomalies([transactions])

Analytics -> Analytics: Calculate normal spending distribution
Analytics -> Analytics: Food spending: μ=1850, σ=250

loop For Each Transaction
    Analytics -> Analytics: Calculate z-score = (x - μ) / σ
    alt Unusual Spending
        Analytics -> Analytics: Flag if z-score > 2 (2std dev)
        Note over Analytics: Flagged: Flight booking\n₹4200 (z-score: 2.85)
    end
end

Analytics -> Analytics: anomalies = [Flight: high_spend,\nGrocery: expected, ...]

Analytics --> Backend: {anomalies: [...]}

Note over User,DB: **GENERATE LLM INSIGHTS**

Backend -> Backend: Prepare prompt for LLM

Note over Backend: Prompt Construction:
Note over Backend: "User spent ₹5,420 in May, up 8.3% from April."
Note over Backend: "Top categories: Food (38.7%), Bills (24.7%)"
Note over Backend: "Food spending 105% of budget - overspent ₹100"
Note over Backend: "Transport spending up 10.1% vs last month"
Note over Backend: "Anomaly: ₹4,200 flight booking detected"
Note over Backend: "Generate 3 actionable insights and recommendations"

Backend -> LLM: POST /generate\n{user_profile, metrics, anomalies}

LLM -> LLM: Process with LLM model
LLM -> LLM: Generate insights based on spending patterns

LLM --> Backend: {insights: [
Note over LLM: "1. Food spending is 5% above budget.\n   Consider reducing restaurant visits."
Note over LLM: "2. Transport costs increased significantly.\n   Look for carpooling or public transit.",
Note over LLM: "3. Implement a weekly grocery budget\n   to control food expenses better."
]}

Backend -> Analytics: Store insights in cache
Backend -> DB: INSERT INTO ai_insights\n(user_id, insights, generated_at, metrics_snapshot)
DB --> Backend: {insight_id}

Backend --> Frontend: {insights: [...], metrics: {...}}

Note over User,DB: **DISPLAY AI INSIGHTS**

Frontend -> Frontend: Render insights cards

Note over Frontend: Insight 1:
Note over Frontend: "🍔 Food Overspending Alert"
Note over Frontend: "Your food expenses exceeded budget by ₹100."
Note over Frontend: "Recommendation: Reduce restaurant visits"

Note over Frontend: Insight 2:
Note over Frontend: "🚗 Transport Spike"
Note over Frontend: "Transport costs up 10.1% vs last month."
Note over Frontend: "Try carpooling or public transit options"

Note over Frontend: Insight 3:
Note over Frontend: "💰 Budget Optimization"
Note over Frontend: "Set weekly grocery limits to control"
Note over Frontend: "overall food category spending"

Frontend --> User: Display AI insights

Note over User,DB: **SAVINGS RECOMMENDATIONS**

Backend -> Analytics: calculate_savings_opportunities(metrics)

Analytics -> Analytics: monthly_potential = total_spent * 0.15
Analytics -> Analytics: savings_potential = 813 per month
Analytics -> Analytics: annual_savings = 9750

Analytics -> Analytics: Identify problem categories
Analytics -> Analytics: Food is 105% of budget → save 100/month
Analytics -> Analytics: Entertainment is 95% of budget → save 50/month

Analytics --> Backend: {savings_potential: 150, annual: 1800}

Backend -> LLM: Generate savings tips based on profile

LLM --> Backend: {tips: [
Note over LLM: "Meal planning can reduce food costs",
Note over LLM: "Switch to streaming services for entertainment",
Note over LLM: "Use public transit passes for discount"
]}

Backend --> Frontend: {recommendations: [...]}
Frontend --> User: Show savings recommendations

@enduml
